General Information
Purpose and Scope

This API allows developers to access and interact with data from the SolarEdge monitoring system securely, enabling external applications to display and analyze site data.

Acronyms
Abbreviation Meaning
API Application Programming Interface
WS Web Services
REST Representational State Transfer
CSV Comma Separated Values
JSON JavaScript Object Notation
XML Extensible Markup Language
Revision History
Date Update
Aug 2022 Updated documentation of Inverter Technical Data endpoint
Jan 2019 Added Meters API; updated Storage and Inverter Technical Data APIs
Feb 2018 Added disable/enable site access by account
Sep 2017 Parameter updates
Jun 2016 Added StorEdge profiles API
Apr 2016 Added status filter for alerts API
Technical Information
RESTful Design Principles

Resource-oriented URLs

Standard HTTP verbs and response codes

Parameters passed via URL

Supports JSON, XML, and CSV formats

Example:

GET /site/{siteId}/details?api_key={API_KEY}

API Access & Security
API Key Types

Account API Key ‚Üí Access to all sites under an account

Site API Key ‚Üí Access limited to a specific site

HTTPS only is supported (both 1.0 and 1.1).

Example:

https://monitoringapi.solaredge.com/sites/list?api_key=YOUR_KEY

Security Guidelines

Never share or expose API keys in public repositories or client-side code.

Use backend services for requests.

Rotate API keys every 6 months.

Prefer Site-level keys when granting access to third parties.

Request & Response Formats
Supported Response Types
Format MIME Type
JSON application/json
XML application/xml
CSV text/csv

Default: JSON

JSONP Support

Add a callback parameter for JSONP requests.

Example:

GET /site/{siteId}/details.json?api_key=KEY&callback=myFunc

Response:

myFunc({"details": {...}});

Error Handling
HTTP Code Meaning
400 Bad Request
403 Forbidden (validation or limit violation)
404 Not Found
406 Invalid media type
429 Too many requests
Usage Limitations
Type Limit
Daily requests per account 300
Daily requests per site 300
Concurrent calls per IP 3
Bulk request limit 100 site IDs

If exceeded ‚Üí HTTP 429 Too Many Requests

API Endpoints
üåê Site Data APIs

1. Site List

GET /sites/list

Retrieve a paginated list of sites.

Parameters:

size (default 100)

startIndex

searchText

sortProperty (e.g. Name, Country, City)

sortOrder (ASC / DESC)

status (Active, Pending, etc.)

2. Site Details

GET /site/{siteId}/details

Returns site details: name, status, type, address, and alert info.

3. Data Period

GET /site/{siteId}/dataPeriod

Returns site energy production start and end dates.

4. Site Energy

GET /site/{siteId}/energy

Returns site energy data by time unit (DAY, HOUR, etc.).

Limit:

Up to 1 year (DAY)

Up to 1 month (HOUR or QUARTER_OF_AN_HOUR)

5. Site Power

GET /site/{siteId}/power

15-minute power data samples.

Limit: 1 month per request.

6. Site Overview

GET /site/{siteId}/overview

Summarized statistics:

Current power

Energy (daily, monthly, lifetime)

Lifetime revenue

7. Power Flow

GET /site/{siteId}/currentPowerFlow

Live power flow between PV, grid, storage, and consumption.

8. Storage Data

GET /site/{siteId}/storageData

Battery information:

Charge/discharge power

Lifetime energy

Internal temperature

State of charge (%)

Limit: 7 days

9. Environmental Benefits

GET /site/{siteId}/envBenefits

Returns estimated environmental impact:

CO‚ÇÇ saved

Trees planted

Lightbulbs powered

‚öôÔ∏è Site Equipment APIs
Components List

GET /equipment/{siteId}/list

Lists inverters/SMIs:
name, manufacturer, model, serialNumber.

Inventory

GET /site/{siteId}/inventory

Lists all site equipment:
Inverters, meters, batteries, sensors, and gateways.

Inverter Technical Data

GET /equipment/{siteId}/{serialNumber}/data

Returns inverter parameters:

AC/DC voltage/current

Power

Frequency

Temperature

Operating mode (e.g., MPPT, Off-grid)

Limit: 1 week.

Equipment Change Log

GET /equipment/{siteId}/{serialNumber}/changeLog

Shows component replacements with date and serial info.

üë• Account API

GET /accounts/list
List all accounts and sub-accounts for an API key.
Supports pagination, sorting, and filtering by name or location.

‚ö° Meters & Sensors APIs
Meters

GET /site/{siteId}/meters

Returns meter readings, lifetime energy, and device connection metadata.

Sensors

GET /equipment/{siteId}/sensors
Lists all sensors and associated devices.
GET /site/{siteId}/sensors
Retrieves sensor telemetry data (limited to 1 week).

Versioning
API URL Example
Current Version /version/current { "version": "1.0.0" }
Supported Versions /version/supported { "supported": ["0.9.5","1.0.0"] }

Version format: <major>.<minor>.<release>

